  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Mapping the Lessons**\n\nI\'m now focusing on constructing the `LessonMap.tsx` component for an interactive learning station map. The design system directs me toward a vertical or \"S-curve\" path of circular icons, each a lesson checkpoint on the learning journey. I\'m now thinking about how to render completed lessons as tertiary green with a checkmark. I\'ll need to figure out how to represent the current active lesson with a subtle pulse animation.\n\n\n**Designing the Visual Journey**\n\nI\'m now completely immersed in creating a visually engaging progress map! I\'m imagining a physical adventure trail with landmarks on an off-white canvas for our 4 stations, especially keeping primary school children in mind. I\'m focusing on \"Chunky\" buttons, subtle animations for active stations, and lock badges to clearly illustrate progress. I\'m also planning the icons representing each station. I\'m currently working on `/src/components/LessonMap.tsx`.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create the `/src/components/LessonMap.tsx` component, which renders a path of station blocks. Completed steps turn green with checkmarks, while the current active stage has an attention-grabbing glow or playful pulse effect. I will also incorporate cartoon-style vector clouds and trees."
